apCodecTranscodingRealmStatsTable.name: apCodecTranscodingRealmStatsTable
apCodecTranscodingRealmStatsTable.description: The table of transcoding statistics per-realm. The table provides additional statistics augmenting the apSigRealmStatsTable.

apCodecRealmSessionsTransparent.name: apCodecRealmSessionsTransparent
apCodecRealmSessionsTransparent.description: Number of sessions in the realm that did not use any DSP resources for transcoding or transrating.

apCodecRealmSessionsTransrated.name: apCodecRealmSessionsTransrated
apCodecRealmSessionsTransrated.description: Number of sessions in the realm that had a common codec but used DSP resources to modify packetizaton rate.

apCodecRealmSessionsTranscoded.name: apCodecRealmSessionsTranscoded
apCodecRealmSessionsTranscoded.description: Number of sessions in the realm that had used DSP resources to transcode between codecs.

apCodecTranscodingResourcesCurrent.name: apCodecTranscodingResourcesCurrent
apCodecTranscodingResourcesCurrent.description: Number of transcoding resources currently in-use.

apCodecTranscodingResourcesHigh.name: apCodecTranscodingResourcesHigh
apCodecTranscodingResourcesHigh.description: The highest number of transcoding resources in-use in the past.

apCodecTranscodingInUsePercentCurrent.name: apCodecTranscodingInUsePercentCurrent
apCodecTranscodingInUsePercentCurrent.description: The percentage of transcoding resources currently in-use. The algorithm considers actual resources the current codec transcoding consumed.

apCodecTranscodingInUsePercentHigh.name: apCodecTranscodingInUsePercentHigh
apCodecTranscodingInUsePercentHigh.description: The highest percentage number of transcoding resources in-use in the past.

apCodecIndex.name: apCodecIndex
apCodecIndex.description: An integer for the sole purpose of indexing the codec entry.

apCodecPairStatsTable.name: apCodecPairStatsTable
apCodecPairStatsTable.description: The table of codec-pairs being supported.

apCodecPairStatsEntry.name: apCodecPairStatsEntry
apCodecPairStatsEntry.description: statistics per transcoding codec pair. In a codec pair, the transcoding is two directional. To avoid duplication, the rule is that the end point A is the one with smaller or equal apCodecIndex.

apCodecPairAIndex.name: apCodecPairAIndex
apCodecPairAIndex.description: The index of the first codec in the pair.

apCodecPairBIndex.name: apCodecPairBIndex
apCodecPairBIndex.description: The index of the second codec in the pair.

apCodecPairAPValue.name: apCodecPairAPValue
apCodecPairAPValue.description: The p value in the end point A. A value of zero indicates the value is not provided.

apCodecPairBPValue.name: apCodecPairBPValue
apCodecPairBPValue.description: The p value in the end point B. A value of zero indicates the value is not provided.

apCodecPairADigitType.name: apCodecPairADigitType
apCodecPairADigitType.description: The digit type index in the end point A.

apCodecPairBDigitType.name: apCodecPairBDigitType
apCodecPairBDigitType.description: The digit type index in the end point B.

apCodecPairTranscodingCurrent.name: apCodecPairTranscodingCurrent
apCodecPairTranscodingCurrent.description: The number of transcodings for this codec-pair current in process.

apCodecPairTranscodingHigh.name: apCodecPairTranscodingHigh
apCodecPairTranscodingHigh.description: The highest number of transcodings for this codec-pair in the past.
